ector of the entertainment","kjv_def":"governor (ruler) of the feast","pos":"masculine noun"},"G716":{"id":"G716","lemma":"ἅρμα","translit":"hárma","derivation":"probably from G142 (αἴρω) (perhaps with G1 (Α) (as a particle of union) prefixed);","strongs_def":"a chariot (as raised or fitted together (compare G719 (ἁρμός)))","kjv_def":"chariot","pos":"neuter noun","usage":"chariot(4x)"},"G747":{"id":"G747","lemma":"ἀρχηγός","translit":"archēgós","derivation":"from G746 (ἀρχή) and G71 (ἄγω);","strongs_def":"a chief leader","kjv_def":"author, captain, prince","pos":"adjective","usage":"prince(2x), captain(1x), author(1x)"},"G745":{"id":"G745","lemma":"Ἀρχέλαος","translit":"Archélaos","derivation":"from G757 (ἄρχω) and G2994 (Λαοδικεύς);","strongs_def":"people-ruling; Archelaus, a Jewish king","kjv_def":"Archelaus","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Archelaus(1x)"},"G770":{"id":"G770","lemma":"ἀσθενέω","translit":"asthenéō","derivation":"from G772 (ἀσθενής);","strongs_def":"to be feeble (in any sense)","kjv_def":"be diseased, impotent folk (man), (be) sick, (be, be made) weak","pos":"verb","usage":"sick(7x), weak(3x)"},"G792":{"id":"G792","lemma":"ἀστήρ","translit":"astḗr","derivation":"probably from the base of G4766 (στρώννυμι);","strongs_def":"a star (as strown over the sky), literally or figuratively","kjv_def":"star","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"star(24x)"},"G753":{"id":"G753","lemma":"ἀρχιτέκτων","translit":"architéktōn","derivation":"from G746 (ἀρχή) and G5045 (τέκτων);","strongs_def":"a chief constructor, i.e. \"architect\"","kjv_def":"masterbuilder"},"G738":{"id":"G738","lemma":"ἀρτιγέννητος","translit":"artigénnētos","derivation":"from G737 (ἄρτι) and G1084 (γεννητός);","strongs_def":"just born, i.e. (figuratively) a young convert","kjv_def":"new born"},"G751":{"id":"G751","lemma":"Ἄρχιππος","translit":"Árchippos","derivation":"from G746 (ἀρχή) and G2462 (ἵππος);","strongs_def":"horse-ruler; Archippus, a Christian","kjv_def":"Archippus","pos":"proper ma